    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 36.2 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>An Argument That the Infidel Cannot Gainsay</strong>&mdash;A well-ordered Christian household is a powerful argument in favor of the reality of the Christian religion&mdash;an argument that the infidel cannot gainsay. All can see that there is an influence at work in the family that affects the children, and that the God of Abraham is with them. If the homes of professed Christians had a right religious mold, they would exert a mighty influence for good. They would indeed be the &ldquo;light of the world.&rdquo;<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"PP 144.1\" data-link=\"84.580\">Patriarchs and Prophets, 144</span>.</span></a></sup>",
